Installing Spenglr
==================

Pull latest git trunk repository from:
git://github.com/spenglr/spenglr.git

...to a local directory (suggested: ~/spenglr)

Create a file named spenglr.wsgi as below (modify paths to your local system needs):
"
import os
import sys

os.environ['DJANGO_SETTINGS_MODULE'] = 'settings'

sys.path.append('/home/martin/spenglr/')
sys.path.append('/home/martin/spenglr/apps')
sys.path.append('/home/martin/spenglr/external')

import django.core.handlers.wsgi
application = django.core.handlers.wsgi.WSGIHandler()
"

Save this file somewhere in your web server area e.g. /var/www/spenglr/ or /srv/www/spenglr/

Setup an apache install with wsgi (+Django) support as follows (Debian/Ubuntu):

<VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerName spenglr
    ServerAlias spenglrcom.dyndns.org

    WSGIScriptAlias / /var/www/spenglr/spenglr.wsgi

    DocumentRoot /var/www/spenglr

    <Directory /var/www/spenglr/>
        Options Indexes FollowSymLinks MultiViews
        AllowOverride All
        Order allow,deny
        Allow from all
    </Directory>
    
    HostnameLookups Off
    UseCanonicalName Off
    ServerSignature On

    Alias /media/admin/ /usr/share/pyshared/django/contrib/admin/media/
    Alias /media/ /home/martin/spenglr/media/

</VirtualHost>

Activate the about virtualhost definition. 
Add spenglr 127.0.0.1 to your /etc/hosts file, restart your server and voila.